ClientHash and HashNSalt have function called getHash and getHashNSalt respectively, to hash strings.
The argument for ClientHash function is a string, and the output is a String.

The argument for getHashNSalt is String,and the output is a String ready to be stored into
the database :). 

the getHash and getHashNSalt function throws an Exception, so remember to use the try and catch block when 
using this function.